ages with the tools of Cognitive Linguistics. The book is designed for students as well as teachers of English and linguistics, and while the target readership should already have a background in linguistics, a beginner in phonology will find all the basic concepts clearly defined.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aEnglish languagevTextbooks for foreign speakers. 0aEnglish languagexPhonologyxStudy and teaching. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxForeign speakers. 0aEnglish languagexTextbooks for foreign speakers. 4aEnglisch /Sprache. 4aKognitive Linguistik. 4aPhonologie. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aCognitive linguistics.  aEnglish/language.  aphonology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Linguistics and Semiotics  2000-2014 (EN)z978311023845708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015z978311074296108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2005z9783110277111oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2005z978311027717308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LINGUISTICS 2005z978311027714208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2005z9783110276886oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311018608640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311092059840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110920598423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9